    {
      "id": "G1qPttA0zlXwL6rmYCzkZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -658.5731067400643,
      "y": -7637.358483082739,
      "width": 874.5594482421875,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1x",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1641127853,
      "version": 958,
      "versionNonce": 1881229672,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772859893410,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Notes:\n1. cron job running each hour, to run the query and update the cache\n2. the cache will be used to serve the requests coming to top-k service api call\n3. 99% of requests will be served in shorter time frame. Some edge requests\nmight wait for some time, until cron is not completed\n4. the issue is if cron fails, then some requests will come to postgres directly.\ncache enteries can be kept for few hours in order to serve the requests with stale data.\n5. key of the cache will be: window:{window}:k:{K}:{truncated_timestamp}\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Notes:\n1. cron job running each hour, to run the query and update the cache\n2. the cache will be used to serve the requests coming to top-k service api call\n3. 99% of requests will be served in shorter time frame. Some edge requests\nmight wait for some time, until cron is not completed\n4. the issue is if cron fails, then some requests will come to postgres directly.\ncache enteries can be kept for few hours in order to serve the requests with stale data.\n5. key of the cache will be: window:{window}:k:{K}:{truncated_timestamp}\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PRR2l0ZlsBmwIPuG4uRdN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -711.167834004503,
      "y": -7400.817347791928,
      "width": 992.8192749023438,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1y",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2078764909,
      "version": 749,
      "versionNonce": 1762651672,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772860401270,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2. handle massive #writes:\n    Notes:\n     1. infra challenge: do the computation.\n     2. total 70B views/day / (100k seconds/day) = 700k tps\n     3. modern rdbms can handle 10k+ writes/sec\n     4. videos/day = (1hr content uploaded/second)/(6min content/video)*100k sec/day = 1M vids/day\n       total videos = 1M videos/day * 365 days/year* 10 yrs = 3.6B videos\n\n   Naive storage: 4B vids* (8bytes/id + 8 bytes/count) = 64GB\nvideo id and views. Taken one rows and total rows are being multiplied.\n   \n   first solution -> . Sharding ingestion:\n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2. handle massive #writes:\n    Notes:\n     1. infra challenge: do the computation.\n     2. total 70B views/day / (100k seconds/day) = 700k tps\n     3. modern rdbms can handle 10k+ writes/sec\n     4. videos/day = (1hr content uploaded/second)/(6min content/video)*100k sec/day = 1M vids/day\n       total videos = 1M videos/day * 365 days/year* 10 yrs = 3.6B videos\n\n   Naive storage: 4B vids* (8bytes/id + 8 bytes/count) = 64GB\nvideo id and views. Taken one rows and total rows are being multiplied.\n   \n   first solution -> . Sharding ingestion:\n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
