    {
      "id": "hMptbiLw1ZXtyI5XygZt4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -630.581824481928,
      "y": -6597.941919585527,
      "width": 715.8394775390625,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2Q",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1256210157,
      "version": 378,
      "versionNonce": 968312397,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1763994936087,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "notes:\n1. viewevent is already partitioned with the videoId.\n2. the view consumer is also chosen wrt the videoid. The same DB\nshards are updated on the basis of video ID. The #shards can be 70 as\n10k writes possible by single instance. But it will be overkill\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "notes:\n1. viewevent is already partitioned with the videoId.\n2. the view consumer is also chosen wrt the videoid. The same DB\nshards are updated on the basis of video ID. The #shards can be 70 as\n10k writes possible by single instance. But it will be overkill\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "EF4d9kE_CPaPgZfXBVeBa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -673.8594962625734,
      "y": -6441.246901069396,
      "width": 831.1195068359375,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2R",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1301638509,
      "version": 797,
      "versionNonce": 1744994328,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772860414021,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "second solution -> . batching ingestion:\n     We aggregate the data over 1 hour and then ingest data into DB. \nThis reduces the #writes by amount of 2x to 100x. For checkpointing in case if\nsome consumer node goes down. Flink can be used.\nThe #shards required now reduces to 5-10. Optimization is still possible.\n\n3. How do we optimize top k queries:\n\n  1. if we start to keep the tables specific for last hour, last month and last day\n  2. now 4 tables in total, the writes will be complex. The index in the view will make \n   it very easy to get the data of last hour, last day or month.\n\n  ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "second solution -> . batching ingestion:\n     We aggregate the data over 1 hour and then ingest data into DB. \nThis reduces the #writes by amount of 2x to 100x. For checkpointing in case if\nsome consumer node goes down. Flink can be used.\nThe #shards required now reduces to 5-10. Optimization is still possible.\n\n3. How do we optimize top k queries:\n\n  1. if we start to keep the tables specific for last hour, last month and last day\n  2. now 4 tables in total, the writes will be complex. The index in the view will make \n   it very easy to get the data of last hour, last day or month.\n\n  ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "AHpOH3Fqn55LcL0pyZqUE",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -681.3211638109625,
      "y": -6112.802411086305,
      "width": 855.6795043945312,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2S",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1026077357,
      "version": 681,
      "versionNonce": 1459104872,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772862453011,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "4. solving sliding window:\n   1. need to keep tables for last minute, last hour and last day, last month\n   2. data will be coming each minute in the main table. That data is taken and that is \nadded with removal of data of just 1 hour back.\n  3. This can be done via flink also that is not that much part of focus. \n\n5. approximations:\n  1. use data structure named as count-min-sketch(CMS)\n  2. these part I did not get much. [not much idea about this solution.]\n\n6. the OLAP systems:\n  1. I did not get much idea about this as well. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "4. solving sliding window:\n   1. need to keep tables for last minute, last hour and last day, last month\n   2. data will be coming each minute in the main table. That data is taken and that is \nadded with removal of data of just 1 hour back.\n  3. This can be done via flink also that is not that much part of focus. \n\n5. approximations:\n  1. use data structure named as count-min-sketch(CMS)\n  2. these part I did not get much. [not much idea about this solution.]\n\n6. the OLAP systems:\n  1. I did not get much idea about this as well. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
